Key Match Events: Zach Neto hit a two-run home run to left-center field in the fifth inning
Spencer Torkelson struck out swinging against Ben Joyce with the bases loaded in the eighth inning
Post-Match Reflections: The Tigers finished 0-for-8 with runners in scoring position
Manager A.J. Hinch emphasized the need to string at-bats together and get balls in play in the air to impact the pitcher
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zach Neto became the first Angels infielder in franchise history to produce a 20-20 season
Jack Kochanowicz carved up the Tigers in his sixth start, tossing six scoreless innings on five hits and no walks with four strikeouts
